OL,3,CReform has chosen freedoms of speech
OL,4,Cat universities as one of its
OL,5,Cbattlegrounds
OL,7,FThe catalyst was a decision by the
OL,8,Fdebating society at Bangor University
OL,9,Fnot to host Reform MPs, a move the
OL,10,Fparty has framed as evidence of a
OL,11,Fwider culture of "no-platforming" in
OL,12,FWelsh higher education. Senior Reform
OL,13,Ffigures, including former chair Zia
OL,14,FYusuf, escalated the row by suggesting
OL,15,Fpublic funding for the Gwynedd
OL,16,Finstitution could be cut.
